---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog - OmenDB" description="Technical deep dives into learned databases and machine learning for data systems">
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Blog</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">Technical deep dives into learned databases</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-12">
        <article class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
            <time datetime="2025-09-26">September 26, 2025</time>
            <span class="mx-2">•</span>
            <span>Technical Deep Dive</span>
          </div>

          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            <a href="/blog/making-postgres-10x-faster" class="hover:text-blue-600 transition-colors">
              We Made PostgreSQL 10x Faster With Machine Learning
            </a>
          </h2>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">
            For the past 45 years, databases have used B-trees for indexing. Every single one. PostgreSQL, MySQL, Oracle - they all traverse tree structures to find your data. What if we told the database where data lives instead of making it search?
          </p>

          <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
            <div class="flex items-center space-x-4">
              <span class="bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Performance</span>
              <span class="bg-green-100 text-green-800 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Machine Learning</span>
              <span class="bg-purple-100 text-purple-800 text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Database Systems</span>
            </div>
            <a href="/blog/making-postgres-10x-faster" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium">
              Read more →
            </a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <div class="text-center py-12">
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">More posts coming soon...</p>
          <a href="/early-access" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 font-medium">
            Subscribe for updates →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>